videos.description: John Wall scores the Rockets' first two points with a fadeaway jumper, making it his first points in Washington since Dec. 2018.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Wall makes 1st bucket in D.C. since 2018) 2021/02/15 ESHEET

videos.headline: Wall makes 1st bucket in D.C. since 2018

videos.description: John Wall gathers up and floats through for the one-handed slammer.

videos.headline: Wall is cleared for takeoff

videos.description: Davis Bertans gets knocked out of bounds, but still drains a 3-pointer to end the first quarter.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Bertans ends the quarter with a falling triple) 2021/02/15 ESHEET

videos.headline: Bertans ends the quarter with a falling triple

videos.description: John Wall gets honored by his former team with a look back at his greatest moments in a Wizards jersey.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NBA MISC (Wizards honor Wall with a video tribute) 2021/02/15 ESHEET

videos.headline: Wizards honor Wall with a video tribute

videos.description: Bradley Beal snakes his way through defenders and gets a shot up off the glass and in for a bucket.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Beal slides through and knocks down the fadeaway) 2021/02/15 ESHEET

videos.headline: Beal slides through and knocks down the fadeaway

videos.description: David Nwaba shakes away from Davis Bertans, drives to the basket and stuffs the two-handed dunk.

tracking.trackingName: NBA_One-Play (Nwaba dunks it down with Bertans all over him) 2021/02/15 ESHEET

videos.headline: Nwaba dunks it down with Bertans all over him

videos.description: Bradley Beal takes one for the team by going for the lost ball under the stands, then comes back in the game and drains a jumper.

videos.headline: Beal crawls under stands to retrieve ball, then scores

videos.description: Russell Westbrook grabs a rebound and dishes it to Moritz Wagner for a two-handed dunk.

videos.headline: Wagner redeems himself with a slam after missed trey

videos.description: Rui Hachimura tosses the ball to Deni Avdija with the clock winding down, but Avdija walks the other way and Hachimura gets a turnover.
